### 570.

<span id="page_286">p. 286</span>

### OF PAINTING.

The density of a body of smoke looks white below the horizon while above
the horizon it is dark, even if the smoke is in itself of a uniform
colour, this uniformity will vary according to the variety in the ground
on which it is seen.

